<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,460,511,537]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">External morphology.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[465,652,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Male and female</emphasis>
. General color pale brown to brown speckled with yellow spots (
<figureCitation box="[1371,1436,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B, E–F). Head ochraceous, with dark brown basal spots. Crown yellow with 2 short black stripes medially, eyes and ocelli dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[416,484,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B, E–F, I–J). Face ochraceous, with black markings (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1194,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
I–J). Pronotum dark, with numerous yellow spots. Scutellum brown, with yellow plaque (
<figureCitation box="[922,989,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B, E–F). Forewing light brown with numerous darker brown markings arranged symmetrically, apical cells fuscous, venation dark brown with inconspicuous yellow spots; male with one median spot on subapex of clavus, one spot on costal margin about 4/5 from base, ochraceous, apical cells fuscous; female with one spot on apex of clavus, two spots on costal margin about 1/3 and 2/3 distance from base, respectively (
<figureCitation box="[659,784,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1 B, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
Medium sized, robust species (
<figureCitation box="[550,617,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B). Head with anterior margin broadly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1209,1276,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B). Crown wide and short, roundly produced beyond anterior margin of eyes, interocular width greater than width of eyes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
A–B, E–F). Face with clypellus short, not inflated, similar in shape in male and female, constricted in apical half, apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[318,384,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[152,255,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[225,1364,187,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[219,1368,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1 A–L. A–D Habitus of Thagria species, dorsal view; E–H. habitus of Thagria species, lateral view; I–L. faces of Thagria species. A, E, I. T. trifurcata sp. nov., male; B, F, J. T. trifurcata sp. nov., female; C, G, K. T. denticosta sp. nov., male; D, H, L. T. fimbriata sp. nov., male. Scale bars: A–H = 1.0 mm, I–L = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398787/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
I–J).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer caudal margin with three acute processes in lateral view; with pair of apically crossing dorsal processes (
<figureCitation box="[349,445,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2 A</figureCitation>
). Segment X process absent. Dorsal connective broadly U-shaped in ventral view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2 B</figureCitation>
). Style slender, nearly reaching apex of aedeagal paraphysis, curved and attenuated apically in dorsal view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2 C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus symmetrical, relatively long, distal region extending over distal 2/3 of ventral paraphysis in dorsal view; gonopore apical; ventral paraphysis asymmetrical, gradually narrowed from base to apex, apically tapered, subapex curved in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[517,585,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D–E). Connective somewhat H-shaped, stem long and broader than arms, with median cleft (
<figureCitation box="[360,450,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2 F</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate relatively broad, with numerous slender setae, marginal setae long and fine (
<figureCitation box="[210,307,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2 G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1231,1257]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Valvulae III, in lateral view, with expanded distal region extending over distal 2/3, apex rounded, with fine setae on apical and ventral margins (
<figureCitation box="[781,848,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
H–I). Valvulae I weakly curved dorsally from base, middle portion narrow, subapex broadened and gradually narrowed to apex, tip acute (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1192,1303,1329]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
J–K), sculpture comprising striations, some branched, arranged longitudinally basally and oblique distally. Valvulae II, in lateral view, with blade-like area extending over distal 2/3; dorsal sclerotised and hyaline area present; dorsal margin with distinct fine teeth, teeth bluntly rounded, widely spaced, distributed from beginning of broadened portion to area before apex (
<figureCitation box="[219,286,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[152,255,1799,1823]" captionTargetBox="[161,1422,191,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[153,1435,181,1776]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2 A–M. Thagria trifurcata sp. nov. A–G. male genitalia, H–M. female genitalia. A. pygofer, lateral view; B. dorsal connective and pygofer, ventral view; C. style, ventral view; D. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, dorsal view; E. aedeagus and ventral paraphysis, lateral view. F. connective, ventral view; G. subgenital plate, ventral view. H. valvula III, lateral view. I. apex of valvula III, lateral view. J. valvula I, lateral view; K. apex of valvula I, lateral view; L. valvulae II, lateral view; M. apex of valvulae II, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4398789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4398789/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
L–M).
</paragraph>
