<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1627,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name combines the Latin words “ 
<emphasis box="[909,935,1628,1653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">tri</emphasis>
-” (three) and “ 
<emphasis box="[1105,1185,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">furcata</emphasis>
” (forked), referring to the three forked pygofer lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1699,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fan &amp; Dai, 2015" authorityName="Fan &amp; Dai" authorityYear="2015" box="[667,1018,1699,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Thagria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biprocessa">
<emphasis box="[667,683,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[698,818,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">biprocessa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fan, Z. H. &amp; Li, Z. Z. &amp; Dai, R. H." box="[826,1018,1699,1726]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" pagination="451 - 491" refId="ref3365" refString="Fan, Z. H., Li, Z. Z. &amp; Dai, R. H. (2015) Taxonomic study of the leafhopper genus Thagria Melichar (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae: Coelidiinae) from Guangxi, China. Zootaxa, 3918 (4), 451 - 491. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3918.4.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Fan &amp; Dai, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
according to the original description and illustrations, but can be distinguished by the male pygofer lobe with three processes, smooth aedeagal shaft and slender style.
</paragraph>
